humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the pathology report, 10 examined lymph nodes were found to be negative for metastasis (Axillary 0/10). Based on the new rules 10 and 11, N0 indicates no metastatic carcinoma in sentinel lymph nodes and regional lymph nodes or that all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma. Therefore, the N stage for this patient is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that 10 lymph nodes were examined and all of them were negative for metastasis (0/10 positive). This means that the patient has no cancerous cells in their lymph nodes, which corresponds to an N0 stage. The Nottingham Histologic Score and other details are not relevant for determining the N stage.
